      • withMutators

        GraphPopulator.Builder withMutators(Mutators mutators)
        Replace the Mutators used to mutate the instances encountered on the walk.

        This call replaces the currently installer set of mutators. A builder initialised with the currently configured mutators can be obtained by calling mutatorsBuilder()

        Parameters:
        mutators - the mutators to install
        Returns:
        the builder

      • mutatorsBuilder

        Mutators.Builder mutatorsBuilder()
        Get a builder initialised with the currently configured mutators.

        The builder can be used to build a modified set of mutators by either adding new, or replacing existing, mutators. The newly built set of mutators can the be used to replace any previously configured mutators by calling withMutators(org.datalorax.populace.core.populate.mutator.Mutators)

        Returns:
        the mutators builder

      • withInstanceFactories

        GraphPopulator.Builder withInstanceFactories(InstanceFactories instanceFactories)
        Replace the InstanceFactories used to create new instances of types encountered on the walk, where the current value is null.

        This call replaces the currently installer set of instance factories. A builder initialised with the currently configured factories can be obtained by calling instanceFactoriesBuilder()

        Parameters:
        instanceFactories - the factories to install
        Returns:
        the builder

      • instanceFactoriesBuilder

        InstanceFactories.Builder instanceFactoriesBuilder()
        Get a builder initialised with the currently configured instance factories.

        The builder can be used to build a modified set of factories by either adding new, or replacing existing, factories. The newly built set of factories can the be used to replace any previously configured factories by calling withInstanceFactories(org.datalorax.populace.core.populate.instance.InstanceFactories)

        Returns:
        the instance factories builder
